0 MRMUD~
{138}
                                    MrMud
{300}
David Bills and Douglas Michael initially started Mortal Realms in 1993 with
the intent to create some nifty code. The MUD became quite popular having over
100 players online at peek times. Dug retired eventualy and several other
coders joined at various times. John Till helped from numerous areas to several
sections of code.  Martin Gallwey helped quite a bit with areas and coding.

The MrMud codebase was released in 1999 when David retired.
~

0 EMUD~
{138}
                                    Emud
{300}
Emud was started October 1999 by a group of friends, Olaf Wiersma, Michiel
Lange, Martin Bethlehem, Igor van den Hoven, and Robrecht van Valkenburg.
Development followed quickly resulting in Emud 2.0 by Michiel.  January 2000
development was taken over by Igor, resulting in Emud 3.0

Special thanks to Lauran, Tim, Adam, and Jeff for their contributions and
dedication.
~

0 HUMANS HUMANINTRO~
{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
{128}
                                   Humans
{300}
Humans are the most simple race in the Realm. As such they make up the majority
of the population.  Although possessing no special abilities or bonuses, they
are the most adaptable and flexible race.  Their height, weight, eye and hair
color vary greatly.  They tend to live in large cities and to be harsh against
all things diffrent than themselves.

{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
~

0 HALFELVES HALFELFINTRO~
{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
{128}
                                  Halfelves
{300}
Halfelves are a cross between Elves and Humans.  They stand approximately 5
foot 7 inches tall and have hair colours ranging from snow white to dark black.
Their elven blood has weakened their strength and sturdiness, but enhanced
their quickness.  Though not as skilled with magic as the elves, they tend to
make better fighters.

{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
~

0 GRIFFONS GRIFFONINTRO~
{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
{128}
                                  Griffons
{300}
Griffons are bird-like creatures from the highest mountain peaks of the realms.
Though they fly fast, they do not posses great strength, which does not stop
them from being excellent fighters.  They excel in the stronger magics, but are
not known to be gifted with healing or protective kinds.  Unlike other birds
they don't see very well in the dark.

{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
~

0 VAMPIRES VAMPIREINTRO~
{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
{128}
                                  Vampires
{300}
Vampires are reincarnations of humans, cursed to live for eternity.  Though
undead, these creatures, also known as the hunters of the night feed off of
the vitae of living beings.  They are gifted with the ability of magical flight
and to see even in the darkest hours.  Along with the weaknesses of undeads,
they are more vulnerable during the day.

{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
~

0 WEREWOLVES WEREWOLFINTRO~
{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
{128}
                                 Werewolves
{300}
Werewolves, just like vampires, are known as the hunters of the night.  A nose
to the wind and a wild throng of rage in their blood.  These creatures follow
the darkest paths of the beast, being able to turn their body into a furious
macabre of destruction, by embracing the wolf within.  Stronger and hardier
than normal mortals these supernatural beasts can change at will to serve
whatever purpose is needed.
{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
~

0 GNOMES GNOMEINTRO~
{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
{128}
                                   Gnomes
{300}
Gnomes are a quirky demi-human race.  Though not the mightiest of races, they
are well versed in their studies of knowledge and magics.  Due to their
familiarity with such lore, they tend to be more resistant to magics.  They can
however, suffer tremendously from physical attacks.  They most often prefer an
evening at home with a magical tome, a loaf of pipeweed bread, and a cup of ale
over venturing out into the realms.

{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
~

0 ELVES ELFINTRO~
{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
{128}
                                    Elves
{300}
Elves are tall, slender creatures with an affinity for the woods and nature.
They are distant cousins to the Pixies and share the intelligence and
dexterity of that winged race to a lesser degree.  With a lighter frame than
humans, they make up their lack in strength and stamina with their superior
agility, both in thought and movement.  Elves prefer to stay close to nature
and away from dark magic and the violent ways of a warrior.
{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
~

0 ORCS ORCINTRO~
{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
{128}
                                    Orcs
{300}
Orcs are large and dull of wit, with short but broad bodies.  Their poor
mental abilities is offset by an iron constitution, coupled with abnormal
strength.  They fear magic, and brute combat is the natural call which stirs
in the soul of an Orc.  They stand approximately five to seven feet tall and
see perfectly during the night.

{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
~

0 OGRES OGREINTRO~
{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
{128}
                                    Ogres
{300}
Ogres stand from six to nine feet tall in height and are known for their
muscle-packed bodies that can weigh from three to four hundred pounds.
Most are relatively hairless, their bodies covered with small, boney growths.
Ogres inherit great physical attributes and healing powers from their distant
ancestry, wherein lies the hints of giant blood.

{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
~

0 DARKELVES DARKELFINTRO~
{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
{128}
                                  Darkelves
{300}
Darkelves, better known as drow are the darker, more evil cousins of Elves.
They were once part of the community of Elves which roams the forest today,
but have long since moved under ground, building vast subterranean cities
and complex networks of caves.  They are lightning fast, and see with ease
in the darkest pits of the earth.  Their nature forces them to choose for
the dark magics or the glory of the battle fields.
{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
~

0 DRAGONS DRAGONINTRO~
{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
{128}
                                   Dragons
{300}
Majestic, and respected as the wisest of all noble creatures, the name strikes
fear and awe into the hearts of all in its presence.  Dragons have grown
scarce over the ages.  They are armored both above and below, with strength
beyond that of mortal comprehension.  Dragons posess the ability to fly amongst
the clouds, which is the pride and purpose of all dragon life.

{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
~

0 DWARVES DWARFINTRO~
{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
{128}
                                   Dwarves
{300}
Dwarves are a race of mountain and underground dwellers.  Naturally resistant
to magic, and having the strength and constitution of ages, these stalwart men
are fearsome warriors.  Dwarves can see in the dark and move at a fairly
normal rate of speed.  A dwarf can be described as rough, dark eyes and tanned
skin, the smell of forge and earth exude from their bodies.

{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
~

0 HOBBITS HOBBITINTRO~
{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
{128}
                                    Hobbits
{300}
Hobbits are small humanoid creatures. They are a peaceful race that are not
known to be very adventures. They are known to be able to move very silently
when walking barefoot.

{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
~

0 SPRITES SPRITEINTRO~
{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
{128}
                                   Sprites
{300}
Sprites are woodland faeries, or more commonly known as nymphs.  Delighting
in joy and mischief, these winges beauties flutter about investing magic into
the realms.  They fly at exceptionally fast rates of speed and only see in
normal spectrums.  Not nearly as strong as a human, they are far wiser and far
more intelligent than most races.

{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
~

0 SHADES SHADEINTRO~
{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
{128}
                                   Shades
{300}
Shades are shadows of long passed and no longer enjoying the pleasures of the
flesh.  The shade moves at faster than rational speeds.  Able to see in the
night, and more dexterous than many races, the shades make lethal fighters.
The death of their body has granted them wisdom, but the fact that they must
coallese a body makes them slightly weaker.  These creatures retain the
ability of flight since they are not of the prime material realm.
{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
~

0 ROCS ROCINTRO~
{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
{128}
                                    Rocs
{300}
Rocs are giant birds from the high mountains.  They commonly swoop to attack
an enemy from far up.  Because of their distance from society, they are not as
smart, or as wise as other races. Although,  given to flying at night, their
vision is enhanced.  Their size and strength make them formidable warriors,
but they make good wizards as well.

{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
~

0 THRIKREENS 'THRI KREENS' THRIKREENINTRO 'THRI KREENINTRO'~
{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
{128}
                                 Thri Kreen
{300}
Thri Kreens are giant mantis like creatures that run the deep deserts.  These
beasts fight in raging wars of glory and honor and move at astonishing rates
of speed and easily over terrains, making them exceptional foes.  They are
far more dexterious than most races and have a hard exoskeleton to protect
them from even the most brutal of attacks.

{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
~

0 DEMONS DEMONINTRO~
{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
{128}
                                   Demons
{300}
Demons are cruel sadistic humans now turned to the darkness within.  They
have an uncany power to curse their foe.  Far stronger and more stalwart than
some races, the demons are fierce shadow warriors.  Because of their
transformation, they have lost some of the mental capabilities that graced
their previous forms, and yet the natural talent for magic embues them.

{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
~

0 GARGOYLES GARGOYLEINTRO~
{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
{128}
                                  Gargoyles
{300}
Either from the experiment of the Warlocks or an abomination, Gargoyles do
exist and they are close by at all times.  These stony creatures are grotesque.
Harboring permenantly disfugired forms, with huge veinous wings these
monsters are intimidating to say the least.  It has  yet to be explained how
the strength of these creatures came to be so great or how they move as fast
with their stone bodies.
{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
~

0 WRAITHS WRAITHINTRO~
{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
{128}
                                   Wraiths
{300}
Tethered to this realm by some fetter, a wraith is a head mortal who has
unfinished business in the realms.  Since these beings are so incorporeal
they lose much dexterity and strength, but gain wisdom and intellect beyond
imagination.  Slow of movement, but strong of magical incarnation, these
spirits are supreme amongst the magic wielders.

{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
~

0 TROLLS TROLLINTRO~
{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
{128}
                                   Trolls
{300}
Trolls are perhaps the strongest, yet obviously least intelligent race.
Sentient, yet posessed, the Troll's wounds begin to close as soon as it
is cleaved.  Standing seven or more feet tall, with weight above 300 pounds,
every Troll is a powerhouse of carnage.  Motley green flesh covering grizzled
features, allowing only a scowl.

{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--

~

0 TITANS TITANINTRO~
{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
{128}
                                   Titans
{300}
Titans stood up to the gods and are now merely a shadow of former power.
Towering the humans, titans are incredibly strong, wise, and hardy.  They
walk at slower speeds to insure they don't crush anyone.  Excellent at
combat and natural magics, titans become strong in both fields the more
they traverse the realms.

{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
~

0 PHOENIXES PHOENIXS PHOENIXINTRO~
{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
{128}
                                   Phoenix
{300}
The phoenix is a firebird of immortal fortitude.  These creatures shall rise
from the ashes of their former self.  Graced with wings of brazen flame, the
phoenix is an angel in avian form.  Flashing through the skies as astonishing
rates of speed, these birds grow stronger with age.  A phoenix is gifted with
the ability to cast the most difficult of spells with ease.

{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
~

0 DOPPELGANGER DOPPELGANGERINTRO~
{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
{128}
                                Doppelganger
{300}
Doppelgangers are shapeshifters, not much is known about them yet.

{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
~

0 WARRIOR WARRIORS WARRIORINTRO~
{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
{128}
                                  Warriors
{300}
A warrior is the outdoorsman and adventurous free spirit of the times.
A self-sufficent person, the warrior is adaptable and can survive in almost
any locale.  Skilled with weapons and able to utilize some of the finest
armor available, a warrior is physically skilled enough to take on most any
foe.  A warrior typically travels light, but he does have the mighty strength
to carry equipment needed in his travels.

Though not as skilled in battle at the higher levels as a Gladiator, the
Warrior might be the one with the most deadly skills around.

{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
~

0 SHAMAN SHAMANS SHAMANINTRO~
{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
{128}
                                   Shamans
{300}
A Shaman is a healer who prefers to fight bare handed.  Though not as strong
when it comes to offensive magic as other spell casters, their punch will
overpower the strongest weapon with ease.
Though not the strongest magic wielder in combat, the Shaman will be the best
around when in need of healing or combat enhancing spells.
A Shaman in combination with a fighter is strongly suggested for players who
desire to multi-play.

{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
~

0 MARAUDER MARAUDERS MARAUDERINTRO~
{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
{128}
                                  Marauders
{300}
The marauder is a dark character which makes use of many skills often deemed
improper by the rest of society.  They are known to haunt the darkest roads and
alleys.  The skills of the marauder reflect his way of life, be it sneaking,
peeking into others' inventories, picking locks, or attacking from behind
with deadly backstabs.  It all sprung forth from the dirty city streets.

Though not the strongest fighters Marauders are always useful when there is a
lock that needs pryed, or an item that one wishes to acquire without detection.

Marauders are strongly advised for players new to muds or Storms of Time.
{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
~

0 DRUID DRUIDS DRUIDINTRO~
{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
{128}
                                   Druids
{300}
Druids are the magic wielders who excel in the protective and natural magics.
Though not as strong when it comes to offensive magic as other spell casters,
their protective auras make them a good companion for a group of adventurers
exploring the realms.

Alhough not the strongest magic wielder in combat, the Druid will be the best
choice when in need of protective spells.

A Druid in combination with a Shaman is strongly suggested for players who
desire to multi-play spell casters.
{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
~

0 SORCERER SORCERERS SORCERERINTRO~
{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
{128}
                                  Sorcerers
{300}
Sorcerers are the supreme offensive magic wielders who excel in brute magical
destruction.  Being weak in the beginning of their lives, they grow stronger
once they have mastered their acid blast and trickery cantrips which might
scare off most opponents once they hit them.

Though not the best companion when it comes to protective spells, one might
find the Sorcerer quite useful to weaken your foes.

A Sorcerer in combination with a Shaman and a fighter goes along well at the
higher levels for players who desire to multi-play.
{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
~

0 WARLOCK WARLOCKS WARLOCKINTRO~
{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
{128}
                                  Warlocks
{300}
Warlocks are the most scholarly of the greater schools of magic, and have
spent millenia furthering the knowledge of their guild.  As a result, they
have at their control, some of the most powerful spells in the realms.

Warlocks can bend the fabric of the universe to suit their desires, allowing
them to transfer objects and people across vast distances, magically.

Warlocks also study the nature of death, and are capable of giving some form
of twisted life force back into the bodies of the slain, as well as tap the
life force of other living creatures.

Warlocks are very difficult for players new to muds or Storms of Time.
{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
~

0 NINJA NINJAS NINJAINTRO~
{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
{128}
                                   Ninjas
{300}
Ninjas are the members of the darkest profession, and are generally shunned
by the more reputable members of society.  They learn the art of killing
while unseen, and have developed many skills to allow them to sneak around
unseen, and unheard.

Though not the strongest fighters, Ninjas are very likely to finish off where
someone else left off.

Ninjas can become fearfull opponents at higher level when multiclassed to
a warrior for enhanced damage to improve their knifing skill.
{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
~

0 GLADIATOR GLADIATORS GLADIATORINTRO~
{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
{128}
                                 Gladiators
{300}
Gladiators are those with a death wish who risk a certain death in the arena.
That which doesn't kill you will make you stronger, and some of them end up as
deadly fighting machines, known to be able to do hazardous damage in the blink
of an eye.

Some look down on their boring overdose of hack and slash.  Most fear the
cold steel destruction they represent.

Gladiators might be difficult for players new to muds due to the fact that
they gain most of their strength at higher level and from equipment.

{038}
--=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=--
~

